results.name: Number of distinct values obtained when Euler phi (A000010) is applied to the divisors of n.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..65537
formula: a(n) = A319695(n) + [n (mod 4) != 2], where [ ] is the Iverson bracket, resulting 0 when n = 2 mod 4, and 1 otherwise.
example: For n = 6, it has four divisors: 1, 2, 3 and 6, and applying A000010 to these gives 1, 1, 2, 2, with just two distinct values, thus a(6) = 2.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Oct 02 2018
